OL,3,CCost of household waste collection in
OL,4,CGuernsey increases for 2026
OL,6,FGuernsey Waste operations manager,
OL,7,FRachel Lowe, explained that the
OL,8,Fcurrent charges paid by households and
OL,9,Fbusinesses do not fully cover the cost
OL,10,Fof providing waste management services.
OL,12,FShe added, "we recognise that any
OL,13,Fincrease in charges is challenging for
OL,14,Fhouseholds and businesses.
OL,16,F"However, like many organisations, our
OL,17,Foperations are affected by ongoing
OL,18,Finflationary pressures, and without
OL,19,Fincreases to our charges we will not
OL,20,Fbe able to keep pace with these rising
OL,21,Fcosts.
